Following a lengthy interview he was locked up in a police cell in the town of Kokono as his lawyer and family tried, unsuccessfully, to obtain bail for him.

The Commission of Inquiry found in September last year that the Rabaul Queen was not seaworthy, unsafe and should never have departed on its final voyage.

The commission found that weather and sea conditions at the time she ship capsized were gale force and it should not have been at sea.

